<ue5><m0>Students to attend<ql>
gay and lesbian prom<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>TORONTO <m0>(--) Homosexual high school students will have their own party next month, Toronto's first gay and lesbian prom.<ep>
   Toronto school trustee John Campey said the June 14 prom is sponsored by the public school board's Triangle program but is open to any gay and lesbian student in Toronto.<ep>
   They're hoping about 150 students and adults will attend, he said.<ep>
   Triangle is a transitional program that opened its doors last fall for gay and lesbian high school students.<ql>
