<ue5><m0>Convicted killer<ql>
gets birthday visit<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>TORONTO <m0>(--) The mother and sister of convicted killer Karla Homolka visited her in prison Saturday to mark her 26th birthday, says the woman's father.<ep>
   But Karel Homolka told The Toronto Sun there was no party for Karla, who is serving 12 years in prison after pleading guilty in July 1993 to manslaughter in the deaths of teenagers Kristen French and Leslie Mahaffy.<ep>
   She also admitted she and ex-husband Paul Bernardo drugged and sexually assaulted her 15-year-old sister Tammy, who later died, apparently after choking on her own vomit.<ep>
   He said his wife, Dorothy, and daughter Lori arrived at the prison for women in Kingston, Ont., Thursday to spend a few days with Karla in a ``little house'' on prison grounds.<ep>
   He said his daughter would probably get ``a birthday card, that's about it . . . the gift is we go there every five weeks.''<ql>
